WEBVTT

00:00.578 --> 00:02.841
Jim Smith went to church one Sunday morning.

00:04.243 --> 00:08.669
He heard the organist miss a note during the prelude, and he winced.

00:10.111 --> 00:14.477
He saw a teenager talking when everyone was supposed to be bowed in silent prayer.

00:14.537 --> 00:20.725
He felt like the usher was watching to see what he put in the offering plate, and it made him mad.

00:22.027 --> 00:27.314
He caught the preacher making a slip of the tongue five times in the sermon by actual count.

00:28.482 --> 00:37.755
As he slipped out through the side door during the closing hymn, he muttered to himself, never again, what a bunch of losers and hypocrites.

00:39.718 --> 00:42.522
Ron Jones went to church one Sunday morning.

00:43.444 --> 00:50.454
He heard the organist play an arrangement of a mighty fortress is our God, and he thrilled at the majesty of it.

00:51.315 --> 00:56.082
He heard a youth take a moment in the service to speak her simple moving message

00:56.162 --> 00:59.086
of the difference her faith makes in her life.

01:00.027 --> 01:06.957
He was glad to see this church was sharing in a special offering for the hungry children of Nigeria.

01:07.718 --> 01:14.387
He especially appreciated the sermon that Sunday and answered a question that had bothered him for a long, long time.

01:15.168 --> 01:22.898
He thought as he walked out the doors of the church, how can a person come here and not feel the presence of God?

01:24.066 --> 01:33.097
Both men went to the same church on the same Sunday morning, and each found exactly what he was looking for.

01:36.081 --> 01:38.845
Most of the time we hear what we want to hear, don't we?

01:41.048 --> 01:43.971
Or we hear what we are looking for.

01:45.213 --> 01:52.402
After our great Easter services last week, I wanted to begin a teaching series called Becoming Completely Committed.

01:52.738 --> 02:01.287
And I'm excited about this service because the series, excuse me, because I know it will help me become more committed in my Christian walk.

02:01.307 --> 02:04.530
And my prayer is that it will help you as well.

02:05.491 --> 02:09.675
Now I've preached on the story of Nicodemus in John chapter three before.

02:09.695 --> 02:20.146
In that message, we talked about the Aramaic words that Jesus used when speaking to Nicodemus and how they had multiple meaning.

02:20.802 --> 02:26.428
Nicodemus was mentally stuck with the physical meaning of being born again.

02:26.528 --> 02:32.495
And here's what he is expecting as in put back into your mother's womb and reborn.

02:33.516 --> 02:37.600
I always think when I read that scripture that every mother in the building probably winches.

02:41.524 --> 02:47.471
When repeating it back to Jesus, Nicodemus literally uses a term that means physically reborn.

02:48.131 --> 02:50.674
But Jesus meaning was to be reborn

02:50.914 --> 02:55.039
from above, born from above.

02:55.961 --> 02:59.545
Now I just wanted to remind you of that message, not rehash it.

02:59.565 --> 03:01.788
Today I want to look at a next step.

03:02.669 --> 03:09.498
In other words, what does being born from above really mean in our life?

03:09.518 --> 03:14.625
How does that look in our lives?

03:14.645 --> 03:18.610
So as a reminder, Nicodemus was a member of the Sanhedrin.

03:19.202 --> 03:27.450
an elite group of community and religious leaders, and he was an admirer of Jesus for some time he had been.

03:27.490 --> 03:33.396
And listening to the teaching of Jesus, he couldn't help but be inspired by Jesus' words.

03:35.458 --> 03:47.250
He watched as Jesus worked incredible, incredible miracles, but it wasn't just his power that was impressive, it was his compassion and his love.

03:48.354 --> 03:55.045
Nicodemus was ready to take his relationship with Jesus to another level, but it wasn't that easy.

03:55.486 --> 03:57.509
It never is.

03:57.569 --> 04:06.164
There would be much to lose in Nicodemus life if he went as a public follower of Jesus.

04:07.446 --> 04:09.810
What would people think if they found out

04:10.242 --> 04:17.493
that Nicodemus was an admirer of this homeless carpenter turned rabbi from a town called Galilee.

04:17.553 --> 04:21.659
I mean, after all, what good comes out of Galilee.

04:23.382 --> 04:30.613
At the very least, he would lose his position in the Sanhedrin and his reputation as a religious leader.

04:31.254 --> 04:35.140
Being a secret admirer of Jesus cost him nothing after all, right?

04:37.464 --> 04:39.026
But becoming a follower

04:39.106 --> 04:41.349
came with a high price tag.

04:43.112 --> 04:43.954
Doesn't it always?

04:46.257 --> 04:46.998
Doesn't it always?

04:48.641 --> 04:53.128
So in our scripture for today, Nicodemus finds himself at a crossroads.

04:54.189 --> 04:58.096
Would he choose religion and continue everything as it had been?

04:58.136 --> 05:03.304
Or would he make it public and choose a relationship with Jesus?

05:04.746 --> 05:07.410
There's really only one way

05:07.938 --> 05:11.301
for him to truly become a follower of Jesus.

05:11.942 --> 05:13.384
Excuse me, I misread that.

05:13.404 --> 05:20.511
There is really no way for him to become a follower of Jesus without losing his religion.

05:22.093 --> 05:26.257
Tell me something, why do you think Nicodemus came at night to talk to Jesus?

05:28.900 --> 05:29.861
So nobody would see him.

05:31.703 --> 05:35.026
And what would happen if someone saw him coming and talking to Jesus?

05:41.250 --> 05:45.455
Could he avoid awkward questions from the religious leaders?

05:46.857 --> 05:47.959
You think that might be one reason?

05:50.963 --> 05:57.771
He could possibly begin a relationship with Jesus without having to make any changes in his life coming at night, right?

06:02.878 --> 06:07.063
He could follow Jesus by coming at night and it wouldn't affect his job, right?

06:08.085 --> 06:09.106
As a Sanhedrin?

06:11.202 --> 06:13.425
Let me ask you, have any of you ever been there?

06:17.130 --> 06:17.891
Maybe you're there now.

06:21.316 --> 06:28.025
You see, here's the reality that Nicodemus is about to be and have impressed upon him.

06:28.907 --> 06:34.154
There is no way to follow Jesus without him interfering with your life.

06:36.157 --> 06:36.958
Let's say this together.

06:37.659 --> 06:40.082
There is no way to follow Jesus

06:40.290 --> 06:43.013
without him interfering with your life.

06:43.855 --> 06:47.219
Following Jesus costs you something.

06:48.480 --> 06:52.866
Following Jesus always costs you something.

06:54.949 --> 06:57.993
You know, I've been a Kansas City Royals fan all my life.

06:58.073 --> 07:02.879
And since today is opening season of MLB, I thought it was good to mention this.

07:03.439 --> 07:08.626
But in 1985 and 2015, I stepped up my fan game.

07:12.418 --> 07:17.002
I think we can call it a fair weather fan, isn't that what that is called?

07:18.784 --> 07:30.395
As a fan before I would loosely watch them and for most of my life I've been embarrassed quite honestly to be called a fan of the Kansas City Royals.

07:31.236 --> 07:35.660
But in 1985 and in 2015 it was different.

07:36.121 --> 07:40.224
I can get an amen on that can I?

07:40.244 --> 07:41.906
Last year late in the season

07:41.986 --> 07:45.152
Now I'm confessing here, so I expect grace.

07:47.436 --> 07:53.647
Last year, late in the season, the leadership of this church actually scheduled meetings around Royals games.

07:54.208 --> 07:54.929
Can you believe that?

07:56.712 --> 08:00.780
We might have left early a couple times just because it was coming on, right?

08:02.423 --> 08:06.610
If the Dirk's family had a choice, we were home watching the Royals play

08:07.074 --> 08:13.164
You know, in 85 and 2015, I watched more baseball probably than I have the rest of my life put together.

08:13.184 --> 08:17.651
Now, we didn't change our life as much as some people.

08:17.731 --> 08:20.175
We weren't the crazies, you know what I'm saying.

08:20.856 --> 08:26.465
But the Dirk's family changed our life to follow and to support the royals.

08:28.228 --> 08:31.954
Many of us are this way towards following Jesus, aren't we?

08:37.282 --> 08:42.467
brings up a very important question for each of us fans.

08:44.209 --> 08:48.614
Has Jesus, has following Jesus, cost you anything?

08:50.896 --> 08:53.398
Has following Jesus, cost you anything?

08:55.280 --> 08:55.801
Think about it.

08:58.924 --> 09:00.886
You don't have to speak up, but just think in your mind.

09:00.926 --> 09:04.850
Has following Jesus, cost you anything?

09:07.426 --> 09:18.626
Most of us don't mind if Jesus makes some minor change in our lives, but Jesus wants us to schedule our work and play around Jesus, right?

09:20.248 --> 09:23.574
Jesus wants us to turn our lives upside down.

09:23.675 --> 09:27.641
As fans, we don't mind Jesus, you know, doing a little touch up work, right?

09:28.984 --> 09:32.530
But Jesus wants a complete renovation, amen?

09:33.730 --> 09:38.396
Fans come to Jesus thinking tune up, but Jesus is thinking overhaul.

09:40.058 --> 09:46.867
Fans think a little here and there is fine, nip and tuck, you know, but Jesus is thinking makeover.

09:46.907 --> 09:54.056
Fans think a little decorating is required, but Jesus wants a complete remodel of the house.

09:56.278 --> 09:59.122
Fans want Jesus to inspire them.

10:02.050 --> 10:09.178
Fans want Jesus to inspire them, but Jesus wants to interfere with our lives.

10:09.198 --> 10:10.519
I mean, a lot of us are that way, aren't we?

10:10.879 --> 10:13.502
We come to Sunday morning and we want to be inspired.

10:17.767 --> 10:20.329
But Jesus would say that's not the purpose of Sunday morning at all.

10:23.513 --> 10:28.658
You see, with Nicodemus that night, Jesus was letting him know that, yes,

10:28.770 --> 10:34.259
He had a decision to make, but that's not the same as following Jesus.

10:36.563 --> 10:45.197
Jesus would not accept a relationship with Nicodemus where he simply believed Jesus wanted Nicodemus to follow.

10:45.899 --> 10:49.104
Jesus didn't want Nicodemus just at night.

10:49.525 --> 10:52.690
Jesus wanted Nicodemus during the day as well.

10:58.114 --> 11:07.448
making a decision for Jesus, believing in Him and being committed to Him or following Him are two totally different things.

11:08.549 --> 11:12.375
The Gospels, quite honestly, don't allow for such distinction.

11:13.276 --> 11:17.843
Biblical belief is more than mental ascent or verbal acknowledgment.

11:18.103 --> 11:18.944
Let's read that together.

11:19.665 --> 11:25.554
Biblical belief is more than mental ascent or verbal acknowledgment.

11:26.242 --> 11:35.135
Many fans have repeated a prayer or raised their hands or walked forward at the end of a sermon and made a decision to believe and that is huge.

11:35.596 --> 11:42.225
But many of those very sane people have never made a change in their life.

11:42.506 --> 11:43.487
Is that you?

11:43.527 --> 11:53.682
There was never a commitment to follow Jesus.

11:54.210 --> 11:57.054
But you know, Jesus never offered that option.

11:57.715 --> 12:00.899
Jesus is looking for more than words of belief.

12:01.640 --> 12:08.109
Jesus is looking to see how those words are lived out in our life.

12:08.609 --> 12:19.524
When we decide to believe in Jesus without making a commitment to follow Him, we become nothing more than just fans.

12:19.544 --> 12:20.705
Fair weather, fans.

12:21.506 --> 12:24.210
Similar to me and the royals, right?

12:26.594 --> 12:30.219
Biblical belief is more than just an intellectual acknowledgment.

12:31.000 --> 12:33.584
It is a commitment to follow.

12:35.367 --> 12:36.709
Everybody understand what I'm saying today?

12:39.132 --> 12:44.280
Following by definition requires more than a mental assent.

12:44.841 --> 12:46.644
It calls for movement.

12:47.425 --> 12:50.850
Am I saying, you know, that one is more important than the other?

12:50.890 --> 12:56.498
No, what I'm saying is you can't truly believe in Jesus without following.

12:56.642 --> 12:59.145
Jesus.

12:59.165 --> 13:07.916
As a matter of fact, John Wesley, the founder of the Methodist movement, believe you can look at a person and the fruit that they produce to see if they really are Christians in their life.

13:10.599 --> 13:12.802
What fruit do you produce in your life?

13:18.529 --> 13:21.913
A quick example is taken from Matthew 25 beginning with verse 31.

13:22.194 --> 13:23.215
Let's turn to that together.

13:23.756 --> 13:25.618
Matthew 25 verse 31.

13:30.338 --> 13:31.560
This will be familiar to you.

13:33.162 --> 13:34.924
Matthew 25 verse 31.

13:41.474 --> 13:46.761
I'm just going to skip down through it real quick here, beginning with the 31st verse in Matthew.

13:48.003 --> 13:53.330
When the Son of Man comes in His glory and all the angels with Him, then He will sit on the throne of His glory.

13:53.506 --> 14:00.573
All the nations will be gathered before him, and he will separate people from one another as a shepherd separates the sheep from the goats.

14:01.094 --> 14:03.997
And he will put the sheep at his right hand and the goats at his left.

14:04.498 --> 14:12.766
Then the king will say to those at his right hand, come, you that are blessed by my father, inherit the kingdom prepared for you from the foundation of the world.

14:12.826 --> 14:15.189
For I was thirsty and you gave me food.

14:15.269 --> 14:17.772
I was, excuse me, I was hungry and you gave me food.

14:17.812 --> 14:19.954
I was thirsty and you gave me something to drink.

14:20.034 --> 14:21.636
I was a stranger and you welcomed me.

14:21.676 --> 14:23.358
I was naked and you gave me clothing.

14:23.818 --> 14:25.320
I was sick and you took care of me.

14:25.380 --> 14:28.123
I was in prison and you visited me.

14:28.683 --> 14:46.162
Then if you skip down to verse 41, then he will say to those it is left hand, you that are accursed apart from me into eternal life prepared for the devil with his angels for I was hungry and you gave me what?

14:47.744 --> 14:49.426
I was thirsty and you gave me.

14:50.594 --> 14:58.963
I was a stranger and you did not welcome me naked and you did not give me clothing sick and in prison and you did not visit me.

14:59.543 --> 14:59.724
Right?

15:00.665 --> 15:09.674
So, so, what, where, excuse me, did the one who did not do go?

15:09.694 --> 15:16.782
Hmm?

15:16.802 --> 15:17.202
Excellent.

15:17.346 --> 15:20.610
So where did the ones that did not do?

15:20.810 --> 15:21.391
Where did they go?

15:21.451 --> 15:25.896
Where did the ones who did not do go?

15:25.956 --> 15:28.399
Okay.

15:29.040 --> 15:33.165
And what about the ones that did do?

15:33.245 --> 15:33.866
Where did they go?

15:41.715 --> 15:44.899
Let me ask you what I think is a really simple question.

15:46.061 --> 15:47.122
Where would you rather be?

15:51.682 --> 15:55.547
You see, Jesus does not hold back with Nicodemus.

15:56.589 --> 16:04.459
Following Jesus would require a commitment that would cost Nicodemus a great, great deal.

16:05.681 --> 16:09.907
As we look at what it means to follow Jesus, this is going to become a theme, folks.

16:10.748 --> 16:13.171
As a matter of fact, we can go throughout Scripture.

16:13.812 --> 16:18.398
Moses couldn't follow God without standing in front of Pharaoh.

16:18.438 --> 16:21.202
How many of us would have rather not done that?

16:22.082 --> 16:28.431
Noah couldn't follow God without building an ark that would bring ridicule from his neighbors.

16:28.531 --> 16:35.881
Daniel couldn't follow God by praying to him alone without being thrown into a lion's den.

16:36.322 --> 16:40.728
Following Jesus isn't something you can do at night where no one notices.

16:41.148 --> 16:45.434
It is a full time commitment that will interfere with your life.

16:45.975 --> 16:46.796
I promise you.

16:50.040 --> 16:51.282
You see, many of us,

16:51.426 --> 17:12.616
have been ushered into the church, whether it's this church or other churches, with churches saying with great passion about you needing to make a decision to believe, but then said little about the fact that this commitment would and should change the way I really butchered that, didn't I?

17:13.037 --> 17:13.638
That you live.

17:14.539 --> 17:16.722
Many of us have been ushered into churches.

17:17.058 --> 17:28.832
Saying with great passion about the fact that you need to make a decision to believe, but then have said little about the fact that this commitment would and should change the way that you live.

17:31.675 --> 17:41.426
We have ordered a gospel that costs us nothing and offers us everything.

17:45.730 --> 17:48.273
What does following Jesus cost you?

17:51.116 --> 17:54.841
We have ordered a gospel that costs us nothing and offers us everything.

17:56.283 --> 18:07.616
So in case someone left it out or forgot to mention it when they explained the gospel to you, there is no forgiveness without repentance.

18:09.218 --> 18:12.562
There is no salvation without surrender.

18:13.186 --> 18:20.996
There is no life without death, and there is no believing without committing to Jesus Christ.

18:21.838 --> 18:22.058
Amen?

18:24.301 --> 18:43.186
If you're one of those occasional Christians, if you're one that comes on Christmas Easter, and maybe if there's a funeral, if you have believed, but only come to Jesus when it is safe in the dark or on Sunday morning, Jesus now invites you to follow Him in the light.

18:44.482 --> 18:46.785
Follow Jesus in the light.

18:46.825 --> 18:50.090
And I tell you what, what a great day to do it today.

18:50.290 --> 18:57.240
Choose, make a decision to be committed to Jesus Christ as we take communion this morning as a church family.

18:59.103 --> 19:01.747
There is no better day than today.

19:01.767 --> 19:11.761
I mean, all of us together, both services together, worshiping together, receiving the Lord's table together.

19:12.001 --> 19:12.402
Amen.

19:13.410 --> 19:21.321
Maybe you have called yourself a Christian for years, but you have yet to commit your life to following Jesus.

19:21.722 --> 19:38.046
I invite you today to make that happen because we see throughout Scripture that when you say, I believe in Jesus, Jesus expects us to follow Jesus.

19:38.246 --> 19:41.170
Jesus expects our lives to change.

19:41.538 --> 19:47.067
Jesus expects us to walk him with him and follow him in the light.

19:47.588 --> 19:47.868
Amen.

19:49.090 --> 19:51.714
So today, take a stand.

19:53.377 --> 19:54.679
Say, I'm going to follow you Jesus.

19:54.959 --> 19:59.527
No matter what it costs me in my life, I want to follow you.

20:00.969 --> 20:01.370
Let's pray.

20:02.732 --> 20:04.354
Holy God, we celebrate you today.

20:05.196 --> 20:09.202
We give you thanks and praise for this amazingly gorgeous day.

20:09.826 --> 20:12.390
I thank you for all the folks that are gathered here today.

20:12.450 --> 20:17.939
And I thank you for the anointing that is upon their life and has been upon this worship service.

20:18.740 --> 20:26.291
We celebrate Lord, the fact that you are excited that we were here focusing on you and worshiping your holy name.

20:27.333 --> 20:32.882
And as you taught us today, Lord, help us take that step of commitment.

20:32.902 --> 20:34.805
Help us, Lord, follow you.

20:34.845 --> 20:38.290
Yes, it starts with a decision to believe, Lord.

20:38.722 --> 20:47.252
But let us make that next decision and that next commitment to do your work in this world that we live.

20:48.456 --> 20:49.861
We love you God in Jesus name.

20:50.825 --> 20:51.186
Amen.

